					<msContents>
						<summary>

						<p>This is engraved in continuation of No. 5 of 1907 (<hi rend="italic">S.I.I.</hi>, Vol. XIII No. 300). which is assignable to Āditya I and is in the same script. Probably it is a record of <hi rend="bold">Parāntaka's</hi> reign, and it registers an endowment of a quarter <hi rend="italic">śēy</hi> of land at Tiruviśalūr, by Perumāṉ Sōmāśiyār a <hi rend="italic">Śeṭṭi</hi> of Aḷḷūr, to provide for the sacred bath of the god Tiruviśalūr Perumaṉaḍigaḷ.</p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
